s:123:"The opener is that small electrically powered box-like device at the top of the door that controls its opening and closing.";i:13;s:104:"Cold temperatures can hinder the performance of the openers motor and other essential system components.";i:14;s:174:"Garage Door Wont Open or is Very Difficult and Heavy When Trying to Lift If your garage door wont open manually or it feels like it weighs a ton you may have a broken spring.";i:15;s:137:"This happens more often in the wintercolder months because spring wire becomes more brittle and therefore weakens in colder temperatures.";i:16;s:138:"When metal gets cold it contractsTherefore if temperatures drop the metal tracks on your garage door will contract making it hard to open.";i:17;s:64:"So the problem might not be with your garage door opener at all.";i:18;s:97:"To help prevent a contracting metal issue always keep your door tracks clean and well lubricated.";i:19;s:211:"If youre still having problems then the cold temperatures may have caused the brackets that hold the runners for the garage door in place to become misaligned due to contraction of the metal in the cold weather.";i:20;s:61:"Check them to make sure theyre correctly in place and if not.";i:21;s:104:"Here are possible reasons why your garage door wont open and close properly in cold and potential fixes.";i:22;s:126:"If your garage door is metal then one of the reasons why it does not open and closes properly is because of metal contraction.";i:23;s:83:"A garage door made of metal usually expands and contracts depending on temperature.";i:24;s:46:"Cold Weather Garage Door Safety Sensor Issues.";i:25;s:59:"Cold weather can affect safety sensors in a number of ways.";i:26;s:126:"When there is an issue with your safety sensors the opener will interpret this as an obstruction and refuse to close the door.";i:27;s:151:"If the issue is with the sensors youll likely find that you can use the garage door remote or wall-mounted switch to open the door but not to close it.";i:28;s:43:"What would cause a garage door not to open.";i:29;s:90:"A broken spring repair is one of the most common reasons why a garage door is not opening.";i:30;s:93:"Garage tension springs store mechanical energy that controls the movement of the garage door.";i:31;s:95:"Wear and tear could weaken the tension springs which could lead to the garage door not working.";i:32;s:163:"In cold weather conditions your garage door opener may strain to open the door which could create greater energy costs to you or cause the door or opener to break.";i:33;s:44:"Reasons why your garage door is not closing.";i:34;s:135:"Check for your garage door sensors Your garage door sensors are positioned just six inches off the ground on both sides of the opening.";i:35;s:39:"Transmit a signal between the two eyes.";i:36;s:79:"If somehow this signal is broken by any sort of hindrance such as cold weather.";i:37;s:32:"Metal Contracts in Cold Weather.";i:38;s:92:"This is actually one of the more common reasons garage doors refuse to open in cold weather.";i:39;s:48:"Thats because metal tends to contract when cold.";i:40;s:69:"The space between molecules gets very cramped leading to contraction.";i:41;s:89:"As a result the metal could be locking the door in place with no give to move down or up.";i:42;s:24:"GARAGE DOOR NOT OPENING.";i:43;s:36:"The cold weather will break springs.";i:44;s:75:"If your garage door wont open chances are you have a broken spring problem.";i:45;s:56:"The garage door springs are responsible for lifting the.";i:46;s:77:"A home with a garage means a secure and convenient area for parking your car.";i:47;s:131:"It allows you to enter and exit your vehicle without the worries of outside weather conditions especially during the winter months.";i:48;s:125:"Very few things can cause more panic and inconvenience however than when your garage door is stuck or not opening completely.";i:49;s:216:"Solutions For Garage Door Opening Problems Frozen Garage Door why does garage door opener not work in cold weather is important information accompanied by photo and HD pictures sourced from all websites in the world.";i:50;s:125:"When the weather gets hot the metal on the bracket and rails expands in a way such that the safety sensors become misaligned.";i:51;s:102:"When its hot and the door doesnt operate check to see if there are any blinking lights on the sensors.";i:52;s:96:"Step one - when its hot and acting up close the door disconnect the opener and open it manually.";i:53;s:160:"If thermal expansion is making the door bind you need to address the basic mechanical issues of the door mechanism BEFORE you start cranking up the door opener.";}}